participating-org.narrative:
Action against Unemployment and Migration '' ACM / NIGER '' is a non-governmental, apolitical, non-denominational and non-profit organization, created in August 2017 and approved by the State of Niger by decree n ° 00168 / MISPD / ACR / DGAPJ / DLP of March 12, 2018.
The Organization intervenes in three (3) domains declined as follows:
Job Creation;
Food safety ;
Irregular Migration.
The vision of the NGO ACM-NIGER is to make the primary sector a means of fight against Youth Unemployment and Underemployment, Rural Food Insecurity and Irregular Migration, in other words, the driving force behind the development of our country.
Specifically, the Organization aims to:
Contribute significantly to the reduction of unemployment and underemployment of young people through the developmentof the private sector;
fight against food insecurity in rural areas;
Fight against Irregular Migration.
The expected results acrossthe Organization are:
The eradication of youth unemployment and underemployment is effective through the development of the privatesector;
Food security is guaranteed in rural areas;
The irregular migration rate is significantly reduced.
